  "translations": {
    "en": "And you, O people of Egypt! Let your speech be confirmed by your conduct, and your public life by your private life. Let not your tongues contradict your hearts. Know that a leader who guides to the right path cannot be equated to one who leads to ruination, nor does the successor of the Prophet compare with his adversary. I am not anxious about a believer or an unbeliever doing you harm – Allah prevents the believer because of his faith, and constrains the unbeliever because of his disbelief. But I worry about the hypocrite, who says what you approve but does what you disapprove.",
